  "texts": [
    "Applied to a self-triage use case, a person experiencing severe pain (10 out of 10) would not seek additional information and visit the emergency department based on this information alone.",
    "If the pain is -according to systematic design principles -changed to 2 out of 10, participants might use other decision-making strategies and not rely solely on pain as the most important information but also include additional cues.",
    "Another example of the influence of interrelations between cues is myocardial infarctions.",
    "Given the varying prevalences of myocardial infarctions by age 25, shortness of breath and chest pain are most likely signs of a myocardial infarction among 85-year old patients, whereas the same symptoms among 20-year-old patients most likely indicate a panic attack.",
    "The correct self-triage level and also the decisions participants make for these two cases might thus be different."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Given the varying prevalences of myocardial infarctions by age 25, shortness of breath and chest pain are most likely signs of a myocardial infarction among 85-year old patients, whereas the same symptoms among 20-year-old patients most likely indicate a panic attack."
  ]
